lead_paragraph: Annika Sorenstam shot her second consecutive four-under 68 to increase her lead to seven strokes after the third round of the Dubai Ladies Masters, the season-ending tournament on the women’s European Tour. Sorenstam had a 15-under 201 total on the Emirates Golf Club’s Majlis Course. Karrie Webb of Australia was second after a 70, and Helen Alfredsson of Sweden, the European Solheim Cup captain, was seven under after a 68.
